Reference joins two entities together. (Reference of Course IDs can connect a Student with multiple courses) 
Prime attributes ('Course ID' is a prime attribute of the entity "Course") [underlined] 
Reference attributes ('Course ID' passed as a reference inside the 'Student' entity)

Column - attribute
Row - tuple
"Keys" are the backbone of RDBMS
Key attributes : Unique identification. (Particularyly targets a record or tuple)
Keys help to identify the required row of data in a table. 
Keys ensure to identify the required record despite of having 'duplication' challenges. 
i. Primary key : Unique. [Aadhar card] In a table one column can contain only one primary key. 
ii. Candidate key : Main role / responsibility is to identify a tuple from the table of record. 
